# GitHub Repository Optimization

## .gitattributes Configuration

Always include a `.gitattributes` file to optimize GitHub's language detection and file handling:

```gitattributes
# Linguist overrides for GitHub language detection
*.md linguist-detectable=true
*.md linguist-documentation=false

# Mark vendor/generated directories
.cursor/** linguist-documentation
node_modules/** linguist-vendored
bun.lock linguist-generated=true

# Mark test/config files appropriately  
*.config.ts linguist-language=TypeScript
*.config.js linguist-language=JavaScript
test/** linguist-detectable=false
e2e/** linguist-detectable=false

# Ensure proper language detection
apps/**/src/**/*.ts linguist-detectable=true
apps/**/src/**/*.vue linguist-detectable=true
src/**/*.ts linguist-detectable=true
packages/**/*.ts linguist-detectable=true
```

**Benefits:**
- Accurate language statistics in GitHub
- Hides test/config noise from language bar
- Marks generated files appropriately
- Better project presentation

## README.md Professional Structure

### Header Section

Always use centered header with comprehensive badges:

```markdown
# 🎯 Project Name

<div align="center">

Clear, concise description of what the project does.

[![Bun](https://img.shields.io/badge/Bun-1.0+-000000?logo=bun&logoColor=white)](https://bun.sh)
[![TypeScript](https://img.shields.io/badge/TypeScript-5.0+-3178C6?logo=typescript&logoColor=white)](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green.svg)](LICENSE)

[Features](#features) • [Quick Start](#quick-start) • [Docs](#documentation)

</div>
```

**Badge Best Practices:**
- Include `&logoColor=white` for better contrast
- Link to official technology pages
- Show version requirements (e.g., `1.0+`)
- Group related badges on same line
- Add quick navigation links below badges

### Required Sections

1. **Table of Contents** - For READMEs over 200 lines
2. **Features** - Key capabilities with emojis
3. **Tech Stack** - Technologies used
4. **Quick Start** - Installation & basic usage
5. **Project Structure** - Directory tree
6. **Documentation** - Links to detailed guides
7. **Architecture** - High-level design overview
8. **Contributing** - Step-by-step guide with code examples
9. **License** - License information
10. **Acknowledgments** - Credits to tools/frameworks

### Project Stats Section

Include metrics to showcase the project:

```markdown
## 📈 Project Stats

| Category | Details |
|----------|---------|
| **Lines of Code** | ~15,000+ TypeScript/Vue |
| **Test Coverage** | Vitest + Playwright E2E |
| **Documentation** | 28.8KB Cursor Rules |
| **Performance** | <100ms edge latency |
| **Architecture** | Event-driven monorepo |
```

### Call-to-Action Footer

End with centered CTA:

```markdown
<div align="center">

**Built with ❤️ using [Tech Stack]**

⭐ **Star this repo if you find it useful!** ⭐

</div>
```

## Repository Topics

### Required Topics File

Create `.github/REPOSITORY_TOPICS.md` with recommended tags:

```markdown
# Repository Topics

## Recommended Topics (10-15)

### Primary Technologies
- `bun` / `typescript` / `vue3`
- `cloudflare-workers` / `hono` / `grammy`

### Purpose & Domain
- `affiliate-marketing` / `commission-tracking`
- `multi-level-marketing` / `referral-system`

### Architecture
- `monorepo` / `turborepo` / `event-driven`

### Development
- `ai-enhanced` / `cursor-rules`
```

**How to add topics:**
1. Go to repository on GitHub
2. Click ⚙️ gear next to "About"
3. Add topics (10-15 recommended)
4. Include website/description

## .github/ Directory Structure

Organize GitHub-specific files:

```
.github/
├── ISSUE_TEMPLATE/
│   ├── bug_report.md
│   └── feature_request.md
├── workflows/
│   ├── ci.yml
│   └── deploy.yml
├── PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md
├── DESCRIPTION.md           # Repository metadata guide
├── REPOSITORY_TOPICS.md     # Topics for GitHub settings
└── dependabot.yml
```

**Purpose of each:**
- `ISSUE_TEMPLATE/` - Structured bug/feature reports
- `workflows/` - GitHub Actions CI/CD
- `PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` - PR checklist
- `DESCRIPTION.md` - SEO & metadata guidance
- `REPOSITORY_TOPICS.md` - Topics to add on GitHub
- `dependabot.yml` - Automated dependency updates

## Repository Description

Short, compelling description (max 350 chars for GitHub About):

**Format:** `[What it does] · [Key tech] · [Unique feature]`

**Example:** `Enterprise Telegram affiliate bot with multi-level tracking · Bun + TypeScript + Cloudflare Workers · AI-enhanced development`

## Social Preview Image

**Recommended size:** 1280x640px (2:1 ratio)

**Should include:**
- Project name and logo
- 3-5 key features
- Tech stack badges
- Unique selling point ("AI-Enhanced", "Edge-First", etc.)

**Tools:**
- [Canva](https://www.canva.com/) - Easy design
- [Figma](https://www.figma.com/) - Professional design
- GitHub auto-generates if not provided

