## Repository Settings

### General Settings

- ✅ **Features:** Enable Issues, Projects, Discussions
- ✅ **Wikis:** Disable (use `docs/` instead for consistency)
- ✅ **Preserve:** Enable for critical projects

### Security

- ✅ **Dependabot:** Enable alerts & security updates
- ✅ **Code scanning:** Enable CodeQL
- ✅ **Secret scanning:** Enable (or use Gitleaks)

### Branches

- ✅ **Default branch:** `main`
- ✅ **Protection:** Require PR reviews for main
- ✅ **Status checks:** Require CI to pass
- ✅ **Auto-delete:** Delete head branches after merge

## GitHub Actions Best Practices

Keep workflows organized:

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: oven-sh/setup-bun@v1
      - run: bun install
      - run: bun test
```

**Workflow Standards:**
- Use latest action versions
- Cache dependencies when possible
- Run tests in parallel
- Fail fast on errors
- Use matrix strategy for multi-platform

## Avoid Common Mistakes

❌ **DON'T:**
- Use generic repository description
- Forget to add topics
- Leave default GitHub templates
- Have stale/outdated README
- Ignore language statistics (fix with `.gitattributes`)
- Use absolute paths in markdown links
- Forget license file

✅ **DO:**
- Write compelling About description
- Add 10-15 relevant topics
- Customize issue/PR templates
- Keep README up-to-date
- Optimize language bar with `.gitattributes`
- Use relative markdown links
- Include clear license

